str2: Not, lest. A primary particle of qualified negation; not, lest; also (whereas ou expects an affirmative one) whether.

str2: To store up, treasure up, save, lay up. From thesauros; to amass or reserve.

str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.

On, to, against, on the basis of, at.
Contracted from a primary word; soil; by extension a region, or the solid part or the whole of the terrene globe.
Where, whither, in what place. From hos and pou; what(-ever) where, i.e. At whichever spot.

str2: From aphanes; to render unapparent, i.e. consume, or disappear.
Where, whither, in what place. From hos and pou; what(-ever) where, i.e. At whichever spot.
A thief. From klepto; a stealer.

str2: To dig through, break through. From dia and orusso; to penetrate burglariously.

str2: To steal. A primary verb; to filch.
